		<hr size="1">currently a 31st bard hunting in OT in groups when i get one, or chant kiting solo until i get a group.</P><P>my question is simple.  should i try to charm adds or should i try to mez them when in groups?</P><P>at this level the mobs really dont hit that hard to kill me to fast, at least not fast enough to be worried about anything.  so the question is simple:</P><P>1.  do i charm the add to turn it on the first mob to cut down on the time needed to kill it, thus saving mana on the healer?</P><P>2.  do i mez it and take myself out of melee if there is more then 1 mob to mez?</P><P>i have done both successfuly and would like some idea as to what way will be better for later on.</P><P>thanks.</P><P><hr><font style=font-size:8pt color=yellow>*Worlds worst speller*<BR><font color=yellow><BR>"For those who believe, then no proof is needed.  For those who are skeptics, then no proof will suffice."<font color=00FFFF><BR>"Pigs get fat, but Hogs get slaughtered and VI is a big HOG."<BR><font color=yellow> "So, reading some of my posts is sort of like having sex in your parents house???"  Dr. Zin</P><P></font><BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
