		<hr size="1">If you're group is killing the mobs pretty quickly don't bother charming them, it will just frustrate your groupmates when they kill one mob and go to kill the next only to find that it's charmed for another 30 seconds or so.  I was in a group in OT the other day with my warrior and cleric.  Also in the group were an Enchanter, a Druid, a Paladin and a Bard.  Between my warrior and the Paladin, with hastes and such we were ripping through mobs pretty quickly and when the bard charmed things it just got everything all mixed up.  The chanter would go to mezz a mob that was running up the hill towards us and it would turn out it was the bard's pet... wasted mana and time.  Wasted my Cleric's mana as well when the charm broke and the pet started eating up the bard.</P><P>This guy was, generally speaking, a newb though, he was getting 1-2% per kill and we were killing on average 4 to 6 mobs per minute, you know how chain pulling groups can do at the ramp to Skyfire.... and he was upset that he wasn't getting exp fast enough... obviously spoiled by Paludal.  When he said he had to go and asked for a TL to PoK.. instead of just running to the book... well, we had no wizard, so who's going to TL him?  Duh.  The druid was going to offer to GG him to Cobalt Scar or Western Wastes... <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>Bottom line, use your best judgement... but your judgment isn't the best, Mezz always.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
