		<hr size="1">"For my info, why does it make a difference if he's using Bravura/Banshee (39/60 or whatever level banshee is) as compared to the ones he's using now - in reference to the not being a group issue?"</P><P>The original post was refering to Solon's Song of the Sirens, which only lasts 18 seconds and really is a waste of time in a group. Solon's Bewitching Bravura (level 39) and Call of the Banshee (level 64) last a minute and may proove useful, but have a level limit on the mobs that you can charm. I believe Bravura is only up to level 53 mobs, which would be useless in a group in your 50's. However, you do get several mez songs between these levels.</P><P>I also believe mezzing is the way to go. I have been able to keep up to 4 mezzed in KC, although when they start resisting all hell can break loose. Also, you can mez one and then target another mob and just melee it. You mez song will stay on the original mob you mezzed, as long as you don't stop singing.</P><P>"And isn't that ring an Inv to Animal ring? How would that help him?"</P><P>It is an invis to animals ring, but it still breaks charm. I just traded a gem inlaid longsword for one to help with swarm kiting. It works great. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle> I tried the camp first, but as was said, the camp is an aweful one.</P><P>Anyway, I say just go with mez....keeps things much simpler. Just try to get the tanks to taunt the mezzed mob before they break the mez. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P><BR>Wizard of the 55th Circle of Knowledge.<BR>Bard of the 51st silly song.<BR>Beasty of the 25th soloing level.<BR>Shadow Knight of the 6th level of Evil.<BR>12th level maker of viscous mana (Enchanter)</P><P>"There is always one more imbecile than you had planned for."</P><P>Message edited by: Wizard of the Shadows (9/10/2003 8:59:45 AM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
